@{
    Layout = "~/Views/Shared/_Layout.cshtml";
}

<div class="post-title post-title-fc">
    <div class="post-title-text">
        <h1>Fractal Chaos</h1>
    </div>
</div>


<div class="container fractal-chaos-container">
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-10 col-md-offset-1">
            <ul class="nav nav-tabs">
                <li><a href="@Url.Action("FractalChaos")">Introduction</a> </li>
                <li class="active"><a href="@Url.Action("FractalChaos2")">Polygons</a> </li>
                <li><a href="@Url.Action("FractalChaos3")">Varying ratio</a> </li>
                <li><a href="@Url.Action("FractalChaos4")">Adding rotation</a> </li>
            </ul>



            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-sm-12">
                    <p>
                        What if we had more anchor points? Does every shape produce a fractal?
                    </p>


                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-md-6 col-sm-12">
                    <a href="~/Content/images/fractalChaos/fcSquareBig.png">
                        <img class="fc-image" src="~/Content/images/fractalChaos/fcSquareSmall.png" />
                    </a>

                </div>
                <div class="col-md-6 col-sm-12">
                    <div class="fc-image-text">
                        <p>
                            Unfortunately not. If we have four anchor points, a square, we do simply get a random collection across a canvas.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            This is because the points are free to move anywhere on the canvas with equal probability. They're not constrained to move away from any particular area.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            We can see what happens with other polygons.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-md-5">
                    <a href="~/Content/images/fractalChaos/fcPentagonBig.png">
                        <img class="fc-image" src="~/Content/images/fractalChaos/fcPentagonSmall.png" />
                    </a>
                    <div class="fc-image-text">
                        Drawing points half the distance towards a randomly chosen anchor with five anchor points.
                    </div>


                </div>
                <div class="col-md-5 col-md-offset-1">
                    <a href="~/Content/images/fractalChaos/fcHexagonBig.png">
                        <img class="fc-image" src="~/Content/images/fractalChaos/fcHexagonSmall.png" />
                    </a>
                    Drawing points half the distance towards a randomly chosen anchor with six anchor points.
                </div>

            </div>
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-md-5">
                    <a href="~/Content/images/fractalChaos/fcSeptagonBig.png">
                        <img class="fc-image" src="~/Content/images/fractalChaos/fcSeptagonSmall.png" />
                    </a>
                    <div class="fc-image-text">
                        Drawing points half the distance towards a randomly chosen anchor with seven anchor points.
                    </div>


                </div>
                <div class="col-md-5 col-md-offset-1">
                    <a href="~/Content/images/fractalChaos/fcOctagonBig.png">
                        <img class="fc-image" src="~/Content/images/fractalChaos/fcOctagonSmall.png" />
                    </a>
                    <div class="fc-image-text">
                        Drawing points half the distance towards a randomly chosen anchor with eight anchor points.
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-md-12">
                    <p>
                        As we increase the number of anchor points, it doesn't seem to produce any especially interesting fractal structures.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        However, we can put an additional constraint to the rules. At the moment, we roll a die to select which anchor point we move towards. We may end up rolling the same anchor point over and over again.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        So let's add the constraint that if we roll the same anchor point as we had on the last iteration, we roll again until we select a different one.
                    </p>
                    
                    
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-md-6">
                    <a href="~/Content/images/fractalChaos/fcSquareNoRepeatBig.png">
                        <img class="fc-image" src="~/Content/images/fractalChaos/fcSquareNoRepeatSmall.png" />
                    </a>
                    
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-6">
                    <p>
                        This simple change to the rules transforms the random collection to this remarkable fractal structure.
                    </p>

                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-md-12">
                    <a href="~/Content/images/fractalChaos/fcPentagonNoRepeatBig.png">
                        <img class="fc-image" src="~/Content/images/fractalChaos/fcPentagonNoRepeatSmall.png" />
                    </a>

                </div>
            </div>


            
          
